---
const sections = [
  ['Magnetic field likelihood', 'Estimated from mass, density proxy, tidal-locking risk, and system age. Vigil weights this highly because atmospheric survival depends on long-term shielding.'],
  ['Habitable zone score', 'Computed from stellar luminosity and orbital distance when both are available. The score peaks near the conservative liquid-water zone.'],
  ['Thermal guardrail', 'Known equilibrium temperature is used as a sanity check. Very hot or cold planets are capped even when other values look promising.'],
  ['Rocky surface likelihood', 'Planet radius is used to penalise likely mini-Neptunes, gas-rich worlds, and giant planets.'],
  ['Data confidence', 'Missing values reduce the final score. Unknown does not count as good evidence.'],
  ['Physical caps', 'Ultra-short orbits, extreme temperatures, oversized radii, and weak evidence apply hard ceilings to the final ranking.'],
];
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-10">
  <h2 class="mb-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-observatory-muted">Scoring methodology</h2>
  <div class="grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2">
    {sections.map(([title, body]) => (
      <details class="border border-observatory-line-soft bg-observatory-panel/80 p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-serif text-observatory-white">{title}</summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-observatory-muted">{body}</p>
      </details>
    ))}
  </div>
  <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl font-serif text-sm leading-7 text-observatory-muted">
    Vigil does not claim these planets are inhabited. It ranks confirmed exoplanets by available evidence, physical plausibility, and usefulness for long-term SETI or biosignature prioritisation.
  </p>
</section>
